                <Viewbox Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="0"  Grid.ColumnSpan="12" Grid.RowSpan="12" Stretch="Uniform" Margin="35,0,0,0" HorizontalAlignment="Left"> 
                <RichTextBox Background="{x:Null}"  IsEnabled="False" Width="680" BorderThickness="0">
                    <FlowDocument>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">Monopoly is a board game currenlty published by Hasbro. In the game, players roll two six-sided dice to move around the game board, buying and trading properties, and developing them with houses and hotels. Players collect rent from their opponents, with the goal being to drive them into bankruptcy. Money can also be gained or lost through Chance and Community Chest cards, and tax squares; players can end up in jail, which they cannot move from until they have met one of several conditions.</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="6">Few rules:</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">1. Player can build hotels and houses on properties if he owns complete color group (monopoly)</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">2. Player must build houses evenly. There can only be 4 houses or 1 hotel on property.</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">3. If player passes GO, he recieves $200.</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">4. If player lands on unowned property, he may buy it. If player lands on own property player must pay rent before ending turn.</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">5. If lands on Chance on Community chest, he must click the Chance or Community chest pile in order to pick a card.</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">6. There is a End Turn button that appears only if you are eligible for ending turn.</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">7. Player is in jail for 3 turns. If player gets double dices, he may leave jail sooner.</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">8. If player was in jail he does not recieve $200 for passing GO.</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="6">Tips: </Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">1. You can check position by hovering over it.</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">2. You can check players stats if hover/clicking on him</Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph LineHeight="1">3. You can manage property options (buying houses, etc.) by click on it.</Paragraph>    
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>
